sentences: Miloš Bojanić (Serbian Cyrillic: Милош Бојанић; born 16 October 1950) is a Bosnian-born Serbian pop-folk singer, well known in former Yugoslavia where he has maintained a popularity throughout his 30-year-career.
He has also appeared in the second season of Farma (Serbian TV series) in 2010 and he won the show, earning the prize of 100,000 euros.
